results.description:
White Rock lake, path above the spillway
This is one of the brightest gulf fritillary butterflies I've run into.  It really caught my eye.  It might be the fact that it was in a patch of dead looking grass that made it stand out so much.  Not many wildflowers blooming but it had found some little daisies.
